main event: A radar and visual sighting of an unidentified object occurred at Truax Field, Wisconsin on March 25, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as spherical in shape, with a series of lights in a spherical form.
The object was observed to be silver to yellow in color, and pink to maroon at times.
The object was highly maneuverable, able to make sharp turns and stop on a dime.
The sighting lasted for 40 to 45 minutes.
No photographs were taken of the object, and the radar data was also not available for analysis.
sighted object: Spherical object with a series of lights
